#   You will find some very useful Tcl/Tk scripts in this directory. See 
# the JANUS documentation for details. If you add the lines below to
# your ~/.janusrc file, which is executed everytime you start JANUS, or
# just link it to this file:
#
# UNIX> ln -s  /home/jrtk/jtk-01-06-27/janus/gui-tcl/README  ~/.janusrc
#
#   you can use any of the procedures without knowing where exactly they
# are located because TCL will find them for you using the index file
# "tclIndex". The index file can be updated with the tcl command:
# (you might have to remove tclIndex by hand before)
#
# gui-tcl> auto_mkindex $JANUSLIB *.tcl
#
